DOCKER VOLUMES
------------------
Why we have to use volume?
it is noting like we are storing data in locally
for ex:
When container was running you may add some data it will stored but by default
but when cantainer will delete automatically data also will be deleted 
to solve that problem volume is on of the thing we have to use
Types of volumes?
1.Named volumes
2.Anonymous volumes
3.blind volumes
How it works?
we will create one volume in locally we will attached that volume to container all the date will stored in that volume
if container deleted data will safe on that volume
if you create another new conntainer we will just mount that volume to that container thats it
------------------------
docker volume ls -> to see volumes
docker volume create volname -> to create volume
docker run -it -p 1111:80 --mount src=volname,destination=which folder you have to attach nginx   -> to mount volume
docker volume rm vol name
docker volume inspect volname
