DOCKER COMPOSE
----------------
Why we have to use these?
when you have a more that one container we have to stop or start one by one it will take long time
but by using docker compose you can start and stop containers at time by using docker compose file
Naming rules for Dockercompose file:
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.yaml
compose.yml
compose.yaml--> docker compose will suport only those type of file name stucture.
------------------------------------
syntax
------
services:
  food:
    container_name: food
    image: shaikmustafa/dm
    ports:
      - "1111:80"
  instamart:
    container_name: insta
    image: shaikmustafa/cycle
    ports:
      - "2222:80"
---------------------
to start all containers at a time 
->docker-compose up -d
to stop
->docker-compose down
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Docker compose file along with volumes and network with build processs
------------------
services:
  bus:
    container_name: bus_ticket
    build: ./bus
    ports:
      - "1111:80"
    networks:
      - busnetwork
    volumes:
      - bus:/shasi/
  flight:
    container_name: flight_ticket
    build: ./flight
    ports:
      - "2222:80"
    networks:
      - flightnetwork
    volumes:
      - flight:/shasi_flight/
networks:
  busnetwork:
    driver: bridge
  flightnetwork:
    driver: bridge
volumes:
  bus:
  flight:
